deck_excerpt: The ultimate Dark Magician Deck without broken Red-Eyes Dragoon, win your matches with pride.
deck_description: The ultimate Dark Magician Deck without broken Red-Eyes Dragoon, win your matches with pride.

This deck involves using Dark Magician Girl and the other Magician Girl cards to summon either themselves or summon bigger monsters in the Extra Deck.  Some combos include using Magician's Restage to summon Magicians' Souls and using Magicians' Souls to send it to the graveyard to draw cards. Magician's Restage also works on Berry Magician Girl. Magician's Restage is also useful in summoning Predaplant Verte Anaconda.  Using Eye of Timaeus, you can summon either Dragoon or Dark Magician Girl the Dragon Knight. One of my favorite things to do with this deck is using the effect of Kiwi Magician Girl to increase Dark Magician Girl the Dragon Knight's attack to higher levels to beat over foes, since nothing's more humiliating than losing to Dark Magician Girls in general.  Of course there's always the tried and tested Predaplant Verte Anaconda into Dragoon combo that's in nearly every deck nowadays. There's also the summoning of Divine Arsenal AA Zeus from two level ones including Magicians' Souls or Berry Magician Girl.  This deck also includes Ash Blossom and Solemn Judgement, although these can switched out for any other hand traps or field traps of your liking, these are the ones I went with.

deck_excerpt: The publisher announced the new titles during the Yu-Gi-Oh! Digital Next event, with one title planned to release this Fall.
deck_description: Konami has revealed three, new digital titles for Yu-Gi-Oh!, Master Duel, Rush Duel and Cross Duel, advancing the digital TCG to new heights. The publisher announced the new titles during the Yu-Gi-Oh! Digital Next event, with one title planned to release this Fall. Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Links will also be receiving an exciting new addition called Arc-V World, and we’ve explored each new title below. https://communities.sgna.org/blogs/rapidos-furiosos/2021/07/24/rapidos-y-furiosos-9-2021-ver-pelicula-completa-on https://connect.dona.org/blogs/stream-vod/2021/07/24/rapidos-y-furiosos-9-pelicula-completa-donde-ver YU-GI-OH! MASTER DUEL Master Duel will be released worldwide on PlayStation 5, PlayStation 4, Xbox Series X/S, Xbox One, Nintendo Switch, Steam, iOS and Android, with a release date yet to be announced. Master Duel is tailored to veteran duelists whilst also equipped to welcome new players to the world of the Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game in digital form. Konami is confident that Master Duel is the “most complete” Yu-Gi-Oh! TCG digital title yet, and for the first time ever, the game will feature 4K graphics on supported devices. YU-GI-OH! RUSH DUEL Rush Duel is Konami’s working title for the worldwide release of the digital Japanese card game of the same name, releasing on the Nintendo Switch this Fall. Based on the anime Yu-Gi-Oh! Sevens, Rush Duel introduces a new ruleset for speedy duels, where you can continuously draw and summon. Once the new rules are mastered, duelists can begin to collect Rush Duel cards to build their own Decks. Popular Yu-Gi-Oh! Sevens characters can also be challenged in Rush Duel, as well as other duelists from around the world. YU-GI-OH! CROSS DUEL Cross Duel is an exciting new title for iOS and Android, with more details on the mobile project expected to be announced soon. Cross Duel will introduce multiplayer action with fast-paced, four-player Duels. YU-GI-OH! ARC-V WORLD FOR DUEL LINKS The hit title Duel Links, available on iOS, Android and PC Steam, will also be welcoming Yu-Gi-Oh! Arc-V World, which will be arriving in-game soon. Based on the anime Yu-Gi-Oh! Arc-V, this addition will likely follow the show’s four-dimensional setting, where there is an alternate Extra Deck Special Summon method for each. Konami highlighted Duel Link’s success with over 140 million downloads worldwide, in addition to more than 65 billion cards collected and 6 billion Duels performed.

deck_excerpt: Stop your opponent from doing anything with three simple cards
deck_description: This deck focusses mostly on a three card lockdown: Starduston, Mystic Mine and Anti-Spell Fragrance. With all of them on the field, your opponent can not: (Attack | Special Summon | Set monsters | activate Spells/Traps ).  In other words, they can do nothing. This far, I could only make out two cards that could threaten this combo: Volcanic Queen and Galaxy Cyclone. Both of those are run very rarely if ever. Normal Kaijus don't work because your opponent cannot special summon. Sphere mode and Lava Golem don't work because you never want to have more than one monster on the field after resolving your combo. And other Spell/Trap removal options don't work because they can't be activated from the field.     Your core strategy is this:  Summon House Duston/Stygian Security  Run into the enemies monster and special summon as many Dustons as possible to either side of the field. (make sure to give your opponent at least two dustons, except white or house duston).  Activate Mystic Mine and set Anti-Spell fragrance.  Activate Ant-Spell Fragrance during your opponents draw phase and Viola, you won the duel.  Now don't attack but wait for your opponent to deck out, as to not accidentaly blow up Starduston or Mystic Mine.

deck_excerpt: If you want to play Blue-Eyes, but aren't lucky enough to get all the cards, this is a way to go.
deck_description: I've been collecting and modding this deck since the 5Ds era when I got Malefic Blue-Eyes from K-Mart. Now, this is just a prelim version of the deck since I have a Galaxy-Eyes deck and another mixed variety Dragon deck I want to build. The side deck to this Blue-Eyes project is still getting edited, so I'll add that when I'm done. Hopefully though, since I'm not as lucky as some other players, this deck can be good enough without a side deck.

Some tips:
  • If you don't start the duel with "ZS - Ascend Sage", start your combo with the XYZ Summon of "ZS - Utopic Sage", because the second throws the first one onto the field, which in turn seeks its "Rank-Up" spells .
  • You can summon "Leo Utopia Ray" using the "Number 99: Utopia Bringer" effect. Therefore, the "Rank-Up" magic that you will look for the most is the "Hope Force", helping to summon the "Utopia Bringer". Before activating the "Rank-Up" magic, invoke the classic "Utopia Ray" on top of Utopia, to get more xyz-materials, and you can use the "Utopia Bringer" effect once more.

  • Zeus : Can be summoned with up to 6 cards stored for its field clearing effect. To do so, use Cyber Dragon Infinity's effect to attach an opponent's monster, and attack with Cyber Dragon Infinity. Then in MP2, overlay with Gaia, then overlay with Zeus.

deck_excerpt: Exodia stall deck with Mystic Mine, uses Draw of Fate as a combo piece
deck_description: Win with Exodia  Step 1- Set up Mystic Mine. Can be done through draw power, metaverse, or terraforming. Swift Scarecrow and One Day of Peace can stall  Protect Mystic Mine with Dark Bride + Solemn Judgement  Step 2- Get 2 Exodia pieces in hand  This makes what I've found to be the best combo usually an instant win  Use draw power cards to get 2 pieces quickly  Step 3- Activate Draw of Fate combo  **Make sure your life points are lower than your opponents. This can be done with Cosmic Cyclone, Solemn Judgement, or Upstart Goblin  If you have the 2 pieces in hand, search the remaining 3 pieces with Draw of Fate  You will draw 1 for the effect of Draw of Fate  Then activate Cardcar D, Reckless Greed, or Pot of Extravagance to draw the final 2 pieces
Put your opponent's LP to Zero.

deck_excerpt: Nothing like making plays with your opponent monsters...
deck_description:
As a follow-up of the Triple SD Challenge for the Freezing Chains Structure Deck, I here post the Triple SD Challenge for the Spirit Charmers Structure Deck. But first, since I went through some trouble building the deck due to motives explained below, I changed the rules for the challenge and take a similar approach to some special decklists posted on OCG. That rule being that I know must use, at least, 30 cards on my Main Deck that belong on the original card list of the Structure Deck, where having multiple copies of a card will count. But the 40-card Main deck rule stays. Now, as for the achetype itself, the Spirit Charmer Structure Deck actually covers 3 sub-archtypes linked together by their playstyle; those being Charmers, Familiar-Possessed and Awakening of the Possessed. Charmers are a series of Level 3 Spellcaster-Type Flip monsters with 500 Atk/1500 Def with share the effect that if the card is flipped, you can target one monster your opponent controls that shares its attribute and take control of it while the Flip monster remains on the field. This Flip monster also cover all attributes on the game, except DIVINE: Eria for WATER, Hiita for FIRE, Aussa for EARTH, Wynn (not Winda, and no, not that one) for WIND, Lyna for LIGHT and Dharc for DARK. Familiar-Possessed are a series of Level 4 Spellcaster-Type monsters with 1850 Atk/1500 Def that represent an "upgraded" form of all 6 Charmers. All of them can be Special Summoned from the hand or Deck by sending their respective Charmer monster and a face-up monster on your side of the field with the same attribute as that Charmer monster. Also, if summoned by this method, all of them can deal piercing damage. However, Lyna and Dharc have an additional effect: Lyna can add 1 Spellcaster-Type monster with 1500 Def from your Deck to your hand, while Dharc can add 1 Level 3 or 4 LIGHT Spellcaster monster. Finally, Awakening of the Possessed consists of Level 5 monsters with 2000 Atk/200 Def that can also be Special Summoned from the hand or deck by sending a face-up Spellcaster-type monster and a face-up Level 4 or lower monster with the same attribute as the Level 5 monster, where in this case there isn't a LIGHT or DARK monster. All of them have an effect when summoned by their summoning condition and a floating effect:
  • Rasenryu (WIND): Return a card your opponent controls to the hand, without targeting. If is sent from the field to the GY: Add either a "Possessed" Spell/Trap or "Spiritual Wind Art - Miyabi" from the Deck to your hand.
  • Nefariouser Archfiend (EARTH): Special Summon a Level 4 or lower monster from the GY with its effects negated. If is sent from the field to the GY: Add either a "Possessed" Spell/Trap or "Spiritual Earth Art - Kurogane" from the Deck to your hand.
  • Gagigobyte (WATER): Send a random card from your opponent's hand to the GY, then, both players draws 1 card. If is sent from the field to the GY: Add either a "Possessed" Spell/Trap or "Spiritual Water Art - Aoi" from the Deck to your hand.
  • Greater Inari Fire (FIRE): Burn your opponent equal to the original ATK of 1 monster they control (you can chose the target, but by how the effect is written, it actually doesn't target). If is sent from the field to the GY: Add either a "Possessed" Spell/Trap or "Spiritual Fire Art - Kurenai" from the Deck to your hand.
For their new support of the Structure Deck (at last, after overexplaining the archtype): Spirit Charmers is a interesting card. As a Quick-Play Spell, you can discard a card to take 2 cards from your deck that are either "Charmer" monsters, "Familiar-Possessed" monsters or "Possessed" Spells/Traps; then you will add 1 of them to your hand and the other is Set on the field. It can summon the Flip monsters face-down from the Deck, searches backrow, which is really good, and adds consistency to the Deck. It think is obvious you run 3. Awakening of the Possessed (AotP for short), not the series of monsters, is a Continuous Spell with 3 effects, where only the last one is a hard OPT:
  • ALL MONSTERS YOU CONTROL gain 300 ATK for each different Attribute you control. And yes, it can stack with multiple copies of itself, like TGX300 or Solidarity.
  • "Charmer" and "Familiar-Possessed" monsters you control cannot be destroyed by card effects.
  • As the hard OPT, if you Normal or Special Summon a Spellcaster monster with 1850 ORIGINAL ATK, draw 1 card (is mandatory, for some reason).
Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin is their Field Spell that negates the first monster effect used by your opponent as long as you control a Spellcaster monster with 1500 Def. It also has an additional effect to search monsters with 1500 Atk/200 Def, but is mainly played due to the negate. Moving to the traps, Possessed Partnerships is a Normal Trap that Special Summons a Spellcaster monster with 1500 Def from your hand or GY, and then destroys a face-up card on the field if you control 2 or more different Attributes. It can also banish itself from the GY to place a "Possessed" Continuous Spell/Trap from the GY on the field, face-up. The last card is Unpossessed, a Continuous Trap with 3 effects, the last one being a hard OPT, like AotP:
  • "Charmer" monster cannot be destroyed by battle, helping to their playstyle and to maintain control of the stolen monster.
  • "Familiar-Possessed" monsters gains 800 ATK when attacking an opponents monster. (They don't get ATK with direct attacks or while being attacked).
  • The hard OPT, and oh boy this is a mouthful, is that if a monster(s) is destroyed by any means while this card is already face-up on the field: You can Special Summon from your Deck a Spellcaster monster with 1500 Def in Attack Position or face-down Defense Position, but its Attribute must be different from the destroyed monster(s).
For the outside support, and the reason I made the new rule, are the following:
  • Dharc & Lyna: For some reason, the Structure Deck does not come with Dharc & Lyna, despite they covering some of the most popular Attributes ever played, and also being the Attributes with the most amount of monsters. For that reason, and also for the possible search their "Familiar-Possessed" do, I added them to the mix.
 
  • Eda the Sun Magician: If Normal or Flip Summoned, it can Special Summon any Spellcaster monster with 1500 Def from the Deck in face-down Defense Position. During the opponent's turn, as a Quick-Play, can flip a face-down Spellcaster monster to face-up Attack Position. I add it for placing an specific "Charmer" monster on the field and then use it for disruption for the opponent's turn, possibly stealing a playmaker, that is if they aren't destroyed beforehand.
 
  • There are no Extra Deck monsters on the Structure Deck, not even the Link-2 Charmers. You can go wild in this section, but for my recommendation, I suggest both Lyna and Aussa for Attribute coverage and to steal monsters for link climbing, Selene for revival of the Main Deck Spellcasters and also link climbing, any Link-4 or higher monster that is generic (I went with Borrelsword Dragon and Underworld Goddess), Day-Breaker for a bit of extra removal, and finally, any R4NK Xyz Monster (I decided for Tornado Dragon for backrow removal and The Lightning package).
Anyway, I hope you enjoy the decklist and for the next time, it will be the Obelisk and Slifer Structure Decks. Until next time!

deck_name: Red dragon archfiend deck July 2021 banlist
deck_excerpt: Red dragon archfiend deck using edge imps.
deck_description: The deck can make some very strong plays. Mainly going for red super nova dragon which is really hard to deal with for some decks. The deck can also easily OTK with quite a lot of special summons and high ATK dragons. The main problem is that the deck runs out of resources very fast and has only little recovery due to red rising dragon's and ede imp saber's GY effects. Super polymerization just destroys the deck most of the time. Other hand traps are also very problematic to deal with. The main play of the deck is to summon crimson resonator and edge imp tomahawk which mills edge imp sabers. Then synchro for red rising dragon, summon back crimson resonator, summon creation and synkron resonator with crimson, go for red super nova dragon, add creation resonator back with synkron resonator and summon it, then summon edge imp sabers, synchro for another red rising dragon and go for red dragon archfiend abyss to get a negate.  https://youtu.be/xNoID6bXtN8

deck_excerpt: Tribute summon with options going first and going second
deck_description: Would like to have some help making the deck better.     Anyway, the best going first board is Mithra - tribute for Thestalos - Mithra effect for an extra tribute summon and tribute Thestalos for Erebus (shuffle a card from hand), send Pantheism and anything (preferably The Prime) then banish Pan for two domains and a Tenacity if you have another monarch in hand or an Erupt if you don't. This rips two cards and establishes what I call 'The Monarch Lock'. Domain with a Monarch locks out of extra deck, and if you have a majesty's then you also get a monster effect lock. You can also just use Erupt as your monster effect lock. Most of the time, the extra deck lock can really shut down some decks and if it doesn't, game two you can side for something like sphere mode or another Caius the mega monarch.  This may sound confusing but trust me this deck is pretty simple to understand.     Again, any suggestions are appreciated.

deck_excerpt: lock opponent's XYZ, Syncro, link, fusion monster to activate their effects and more negate cards to stop his combo
deck_description: the best strategy in the deck  Endymion > equipped with Artemis > add Crowley or if you have it, add Rilliona > special summon Crowley > activate field spell (secret village ) > XYZ summon Rilliona the wondrous Magistus > activate its effect summon Zoroa > Syncro to summon Zoroa the Magistus of daimon > activate Crowley and Rilliona in GY to equip Magistus cards.  I would like to run 2 Zoroa and 2 copies of spell power mastery. I don't use effect veiler cuz its locks you to opponents turn witch is bad for this deck some people may think they can also discard effect veiler to summon Crowley but if you start second and if there were monsters to negate the effect of your cards then it's no use to have effect veiler. this deck has 16 negate cards which helps the deck.  my advice: if you have Magistus Theurgy you can set it in spell zone and when your opponent activates the spell or trap card to destroy your Magistus card use the spell to be equipped with Vahram.  don't be sad this archetype hasn't finished yet, there are 7 support cards left to come in the future ( more negate cards, 4 traps 1 fusion 1 link 1 field spell ).  until next time see ya!

deck_excerpt: My updated Adamancipator Dragoon deck with some fossil cards to add some flexibility or as an extender
deck_description: The goal of the deck is to turbo Borreload Savage Dragon and Dragun of Red-Eyes, Optimal opening would be a lvl 4 rock, Adamancipator Researcher and Adamancipator Seeker. Normal the lvl 4 rock -> Activate Researcher -> activate Analyzer. Use the effect of Researcher and Analyzer you are looking to hit Adamancipator Crystal Dragite to draw a card or Koa'Ki Mieru Guardian to protect the board or plays. Synchro into Adamancipator Risen Raptite to special a rock from top 5. Link 2 for Crystron Halqifibrax to special Researcher or Seeker. Link 2 for Predaplant Verte Anaconda using Halqifibrax. Synchro into Borreload then equip Halqifibrax. Activate Verte Anaconda to send Red-Eyes Fusion, Red-Eyes Black Dragon and Dark Magician from the deck to the graveyard. The Fossil Engine is used to create beaters in the grind game or to make a material to extend plays. A 2 card combo would be Miracle Rupture and Adamancipator Signs. Use Rupture to send Dragite from deck to grave and then use signs to Special Dragite from the GY. Use the effects to add Researcher or Seeker to the top of the deck then draw with Dragite to start your combo. Problems are bricking with Dragun materials and being unable to extend from a handtrap or whiff.

This deck was nerfed recently and should be now used alongside a dragunity engine. Since Elpy now is banned, you can replace it with Hieratic King Dragon of Atum instead. Basic combo: 1 Dragunity Remus + 1 Random Card: Discard Remus to add Ravine to your hand, then activate Ravine to discard 1 random card and add Legatus to your hand. Special Summon Legatus from hand first and then Remus from your GY due to their own effects. Then, Synchro into Gae Dearg and activate Gae Dearg to add and discard Zephyros. Zephyros 's effect in GY allows you to bounce Dragon Ravine to Special Summon him with a cost of 400 LP. Now Link into Romulus then add Dragunity Glow due to its effect. Now activate Glow to add Mystletainn to your hand and special summon it by tributing Romulus. Now activate Mystletainn's effect to equip Gae Dearg from your GY to Mystletainn. Next, activate Glow in your GY to banish itself in order to SSummon Gae Dearg from S/T zone. Then active Gae Dearg again to add and discard your Chamber Maid. Overlay 2 level 6 dragunity on your field into Atum. Now use Atum to detach Gae Dearg and SSummon Darkness Metal from your Deck (DMetal should be in Defense Position bc its ATK/DEF will be 0). Now activate DMetal to SSummon Gae Dearg from GY once again then activate Gae Dearg again to add and discard Baby Roc and immediately SSummon Baby Roc. That is the basic 1 card-combo. It will end up you having 4 monsters on the field and then you can link your monster into anything your like (L2 Spheres to bounce your opponent's monster, L4 Borrelsword of Apollousa for main beater or negations, or L2 Whelp, send Dragon Buster to the GY and somehow equip it to one of your beater by DMZ Dragon to lock your opponent from SSummon from his/her Extra). After that, you can still make better board using remain cards in your hand. Here's some ways:
  • Now if you still have Ravine in your hand and 1 card, you can either use Ravine to send Absorouter in order to add Tracer to your hand, NSummon it, destroy Ravine by its effect and go for Crystal Wing, Chaos Ruler or Borreload Savage (equip it with Romulus and get 2 negates), OR send White or Black Dragon to GY to get the remain, SSummon it and link for Pisty and revive some Dragon
  • If you have World Legacy Guardragon, it's great bc you can use it with Ravine to perform many nice play, like making 1-level 8 synchro (Chaos Ruler or Savage Dragon, but I prefer Chaos Ruler 'cause it can get Synchron by chance with its effect and it can be easily revived) then somehow, mostly by SSummon your Rokket Synchron back with WLG which was luckily send to GY by Chaos Ruler effect or Ravine (if you have multiple copies of it in your hand), to synchro into Hot Red Dragon
Advantages: -Short combos and not complicated -Multiple negations and attacks with huge ATK in case you make the best board -Hard to break after being made successful -Multiple ways to start combo (Dragunity Start Combo, Rokket Start Combo, White/Black Dragon Start Combo) -Multiple ways to beat your opponent (Borreload S. Dragon, Crystal Wing, Hot Red Dragon and mostly Borrelsword D.) Drawbacks: -Totally stopped and destroyed by hand traps -Can easily trigger your OP 's nibiru -Due to the banlist, it's now weaker than many decks (Drytron, Tri-Brigade, Shaddoll) -Can be destructed by multiple destroying unstoppable cards (Accesscode Talker)

It's a bunch of recycling. I made a deck like this about three years as just a fun casual deck to get me back a little into Yu-Gi-Oh and I didn't realize how much some of these cards are now. So definitely not a budget deck but I wanted to add some stuff to it and all of the cards I added are inexpensive so I think you can salvage something for a budget if you wanna try it out. I have yet to try this one out yet so once I can add the cheap cards I'll test it and depending on the results I might edit this or leave it. This was just a way to visualize how I would mix up the deck and what cards I'm going to add.

Use multiple cards in your hand to send to GY or add to hand your 4 dimensional magicians by Harmonizing Magician or Timestar Magician. I use 3 copies of Timestar BC I think it's necessary to have your magicians in your hand and your Chronograph Sorcerer out. If you aren't enough lucky to have your Z-ARC out in your first turn, use Number F0 to survive through turns and Tornado Dragon + Double Iris Magician in order to get more magicians or destroy OP 's monsters or backrows with 02 Pendulumgraph cards.

deck_name: Destiny HERO Deck (OCG JULY 2021) - Post Burst of Destiny
Scrap Raptor True King Dino abusing Bujinki Amaterasu
deck_excerpt: EVOLVED Competitive Scrap Raptor True King Dino deck. Utilizing Amaterasu to the fullest, Anti dark ruler Dinosaur combos, Super solid gameplan.
deck_description:
Deck notes below: Video here https://youtu.be/OKP-I7MLLpk * Goal is to build a both going first and second powerhouse. This is something you ll pretty much see with my every showcase, This is why multi purpose cards like Set rotation, terraforming are Nutz.
  • Just focusing on one doesn't do dino cards justice
* Foolish burial and One for one, effectively "replace misc" the best they can (If misc goes back to 3, I am cutting each ofc) * True King engine is underrated, it allows you to play if MISC, gets stopped One for one can act similarly, * Sadly there was no space for Laggia, R4 removal (Castel or Exciton), Utopia package, Baroness, etc. * Scrap fridge (whatever is called), does increase the wombo combo ability but at the cost of consistency, and Dinos want the consistency more, also in the games where i wanted higher output "Artifact combo", putting in Overtex is my preference over the fridge, truly it just efficiently covers st negate. Allowing you to use resources on other stuff rather then (Savage, dragster) * This video fixes the issue of efficiently recycling Misc, and shows that Dino can be built to handle dark ruler no more. Which are the main concerns I heard dino players have, other then Misc staying lonely forever.
